Line 1
SELECT stc_person_id, SUM(stc_cred)

This tells the database to return two things:

The student's ID number.

The total number of credits that student has earned from the courses included in the query.

Line 2
FROM student_acad_cred sac

This sets the main table used in the query.
This table contains the individual course records for each student, including their grades and credits.
The table is given the short alias sac so it is easier to reference later in the code.

Line 3–6
JOIN course_sections_ls cs
  ON '*' || sac.stc_term || '*' || sac.stc_course_name || '-' || sac.stc_section_no
     = cs.sec_section_idx
 AND cs.pos = 1

This connects the student course records to the section information table.

The join works by creating a section identifier from the student course data that matches the section identifier stored in the section table.

The condition cs.pos = 1 restricts the results to sections that are marked as posted, meaning they are finalized and valid.

Line 7–8
LEFT JOIN courses c
  ON sac.stc_course_name = c.crs_name

This connects the course information table.

This table contains course attributes such as articulation numbers.
A LEFT JOIN is used so that student course records remain in the results even if a matching course record is not found.

Line 9
WHERE cs.sec_local_govt_codes = '11'

This limits the results to courses associated with the specified local government code value of 11.

Line 10
AND c.crs_standard_articulation_no LIKE 'IAI%'

This restricts the courses to those that are part of the Illinois Articulation Initiative (IAI).
The LIKE 'IAI%' condition means the articulation number must start with "IAI".

Line 11–15
AND (
      sac.stc_term IN ('2025FA','2025SU','2025SP')
      OR sac.stc_term IS NULL
    )

This determines which academic terms should be included.

The query includes:

Courses taken in Spring 2025, Summer 2025, or Fall 2025.

Courses with a NULL term, which represent transferred courses.

Line 16–20
AND (
      sac.stc_cum_contrib_grade_pts > 1
      OR (sac.stc_term IS NULL AND sac.stc_verified_grade = '49')
    )

This defines which courses count toward the credit total.

Courses are included if:

They were taken at the institution and have more than 1 cumulative contributing grade point (meaning the grade counts toward GPA), or

They are transfer courses (term is NULL) and the verified grade code equals 49, which identifies accepted transfer credit.

Line 21
GROUP BY stc_person_id

This groups all qualifying courses by each student so their credits can be totaled together.

Line 22
HAVING SUM(stc_cred) > 29.5

After the credits are totaled, this keeps only students whose total qualifying credits are greater than 29.5 (effectively 30 or more credits).

✅ Final Result

The query returns a list of students who have accumulated at least 30 credits of qualifying IAI coursework, including both institutional courses and approved transfer credits.
